{"id":"2101.00363","submitter":"Dawei Shen","authors":"Chris Florez, Jonathan Higgins, Kyle Huang, Thomas Michael Keller,\n  Dawei Shen, Yong Yang","title":"The Prime Graphs of Some Classes of Finite Groups","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1016/j.jpaa.2021.106990","report-no":null,"categories":"math.GR","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  In this paper we study prime graphs of finite groups. The prime graph of a\nfinite group $G$, also known as the Gruenberg-Kegel graph, is the graph with\nvertex set {primes dividing $|G|$} and an edge $p$-$q$ if and only if there\nexists an element of order $pq$ in $G$. In finite group theory, studying the\nprime graph of a group has been an important topic for the past almost half\ncentury. Only recently prime graphs of solvable groups have been characterized\nin graph theoretical terms only. In this paper, we continue this line of\nresearch and give complete characterizations of several classes of groups,\nincluding groups of square-free order, metanilpotent groups, groups of\ncube-free order, and, for any $n\\in \\mathbb{N}$, solvable groups of\n$n^\\text{th}$-power-free order. We also explore the prime graphs of groups\nwhose composition factors are cyclic or $A_5$ and draw connections to a\nconjecture of Maslova. We then propose an algorithm that recovers the prime\ngraph from a dual prime graph.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 2 Jan 2021 03:41:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 3 Jan 2022 04:29:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-04"}
